  "text": "This efficient navigation strategy we report herein, where animals adapt to the first derivative of the gradient, joins other complex navigation strategies employed by multicellular organisms. These include a turn bias, where animals are likely to exit a pirouette better oriented toward the target [CITATION_1] 9 , and klinotaxis, where animals make gradual curvature corrections toward the target [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
